Canada’s Milos Raonic celebrated his qualification for this month’s season-end finale in London by defeating Tomas Berdych on Saturday to make the final of Paris Masters.

The 23-year-old from Toronto followed up his victory over Roger Federer on Friday by overcoming the Czech 6-3, 3-6, 7-5, thus registering back-to-back wins over a top-five player for the first time in his career.

He will need to beat another top player, world No 1 Novak Djokovic, if he is to win the final Masters event of the year ahead of the Barclays World Tour Finals at the O2 Arena that begin a week on Sunday.

