Being in the top nine was required to make the World Tour Finals this year, as Rafael Nadal is absent having an operation on his appendix.

British No 2 James Ward was defeated 6-3, 7-6 by top seed Robin Haase in the semi-final of the Challenger on Reunion Island, although his progress has given him the chance of joining Andy Murray in the world’s top 100.

The Londoner will be up to around 111 in Monday’s rankings and he is within touching distance of gaining direct entry to the Australian Open without having to qualify.

 

